info.title: Google Drive API v3
info.description: The Google Drive API allows developers to work with files in Google Drive, including advanced functionality like Copy-paste files and sharing.

get.description: Gets information about the user, the user's Drive, and system capabilities.

get.summary: List the changes for a user or shared drive
get.description: Lists the changes for a user or shared drive.
Gets the starting pageToken for listing future changes.

post.summary: Subscribe to changes for a user
post.description: Subscribes to changes for a user.

post.summary: Stop watching resources through this channel
post.description: Stop watching resources through this channel

patch.description: Updates a comment with patch semantics.

post.description: Creates a copy of a file and applies any requested updates with patch semantics. Folders cannot be copied.

delete.description: Permanently deletes a file owned by the user without moving it to the trash. If the file belongs to a shared drive the user must be an organizer on the parent. If the target is a folder, all descendants owned by the user are also deleted.

get.description: Gets a file's metadata or content by ID.

patch.description: Updates a file's metadata and/or content. When calling this method, only populate fields in the request that you want to modify. When updating fields, some fields might change automatically, such as modifiedDate. This method supports patch semantics.

delete.description: Permanently deletes all of the user's trashed files.

get.description: Exports a Google Workspace document to the requested MIME type and returns exported byte content. Note that the exported content is limited to 10MB.
Generates a set of file IDs which can be provided in create or copy requests.

post.description: Subscribes to changes to a file. While you can establish a channel for changes to a file on a shared drive, a change to a shared drive file won't create a notification.

get.description: Lists the labels on a file.

post.description: Modifies the set of labels on a file.

post.summary: Create permission for a file or shared drive
post.description: Creates a permission for a file or shared drive.

get.summary: List a file's or shared drive's permissions
get.description: Lists a file's or shared drive's permissions.

patch.description: Updates a permission with patch semantics.

post.description: Creates a reply to a comment.

patch.description: Updates a reply with patch semantics.

delete.description: Permanently deletes a file version. You can only delete revisions for files with binary content in Google Drive, like images or videos. Revisions for other files, like Google Docs or Sheets, and the last remaining file version can't be deleted.

get.summary: Get a revision's metadata or content by ID
get.description: Gets a revision's metadata or content by ID.

patch.description: Updates a revision with patch semantics.

delete.description: Permanently deletes a shared drive for which the user is an organizer. The shared drive cannot contain any untrashed items.

get.summary: Get a shared drive's metadata by ID
get.description: Gets a shared drive's metadata by ID.

patch.description: Updates the metadata for a shared drive.

post.description: Hides a shared drive from the default view.
Restores a shared drive to the default view.

fields.name: fields
fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.name: key
key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.name: oauth_token
oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.name: prettyPrint
prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.name: quotaUser
quotaUser.description: An opaque string that represents a user for quota purposes. Must not exceed 40 characters.
